<P>Project Submittal Instructions</P>
<OL>

<LI>Create a <B>cs2510</B> directory for all projects in your CS
accounts and create a <B>PA1 </B>sub-directory for project 1.  Do the
following to allow access to both Dr. Mosse and me.  </LI>
<P>&gt; fs setacl . system:anyuser none</P>
<P>&gt; fs setacl . src all</P>
<P>&gt; fs setacl . mosse all</P>
<P>&#9;</P>
<LI>Your submittal should consist of at least the following files:</LI></OL>


<UL>
<LI>Source and header files </LI>
<LI>Makefiles </LI>
<LI>Executables </LI>
<LI>Data files, if required </LI>
<LI>Expect scripts, if required </LI>
<LI>Readme, should contain:</LI>

<UL>
<LI>What machines to run your program on (bert/ernie/blitz/linux cluster, etc.) </LI>
<LI>Instructions on how to run your programs, including the command lines to start your programs and anything non-obvious about the user interface </LI>
<LI>Explain anything that does not completely work. Suggest a testing method that shows what does work, so I can give you partial credit </LI>
<LI>Anything else that will help me to evaluate your programs</LI></UL>
</UL>

<P>&nbsp;Notes: </P>

<UL>
<LI>Send  Sid (src@cs.pitt.edu) email about your directory if you
don't have CS accounts;
you can put it on a CSSD afs directory, or send us the code by e-mail.</LI>
<LI>Any file submitted after noon on the due date will be considered late. I will check the time stamps of all files you submit.</LI></UL>

